# Portal Rules

## GAP-06 — All Portals Show Mock Data
Real API wiring is the top priority. Never add new mock data.
Throw an error if API is unreachable — do not fallback to mock.

## Auth
All 6 portals use auth. Never expose portal routes without session check.
GAP-08: Implement optimistic auth with server-side session recovery.

## Portal → Subdomain Map
portal-owner → app.kealee.com
portal-contractor → contractor.kealee.com
portal-developer → developer.kealee.com
command-center → pm.kealee.com
admin-console → admin.kealee.com

## RevenueHookModal (GAP-04)
Built but unmounted. Wire via core-events pub/sub on post-purchase confirmation.
Fire AFTER successful Stripe payment_intent.succeeded webhook only.

## Data Fetching
Use established Fastify service endpoints in apps/api.
No direct Supabase calls from portal UI — always go through API layer.
